ù Welcome to GETHELP

Welcome to GETHELP!

To browse through the online help, go to the ®L¯Index®/L¯ now!


®B¯--- Quick Summary ---®/B¯

®I¯<F1>®/I¯         Get help on the word under the cursor,
®I¯<Ctrl F1>®/I¯    Show the full list of all available help files,
®I¯<Shift F1>®/I¯   Show the syntax for a TSE command.


GETHELP offers four major features:

    ù It supplements the TSE help system with information on undocumented TSE
      commands.

    ù It enhances the TSE help system by allowing you to add your own help
      files.

    ù It allows you to connect to Windows help files or DOS help programs from
      within TSE.

    ù In the help system, You can print out help topics by pressing ®I¯<Alt P>®/I¯.


Some examples of using GETHELP:

    ù If you are programming for Windows, you can connect to the Windows SDK
      help files to get help on Win32 APIs, OLE, MFC, etc.  Or you can get
      help on Borland C++, etc.  Any Windows help file can be accessed.

    ù If you are writing DOS batch files, and you have the 4DOS command shell
      from JP Software (see ®L¯ftp:ftp.std.com/vendors/jpsoft®/L¯ or
      ®L¯http://www.jpsoft.com®/L¯), you can connect to the 4DOS help system.

    ù You can write your own help file, and connect it to your macro (See the
      "MyHelp" function in GETHELP.SI for an example of how to do this).


